#: ../../source/developers/remote-users.rst:11
msgid ""
"If you are working on anything related to users, please keep in mind that"
" your changes will likely affect Shibboleth and OAuth users. For some "
"background on user accounts in Dataverse, see \"Auth Modes: Local vs. "
"Remote vs. Both\" in the :doc:`/installation/config` section of the "
"Installation Guide."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/developers/remote-users.rst:13
msgid ""
"Rather than setting up Shibboleth on your laptop, developers are advised "
"to simply add a value to their database to enable Shibboleth \"dev mode\""
" like this:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/developers/remote-users.rst:15
msgid ""
"``curl http://localhost:8080/api/admin/settings/:DebugShibAccountType -X "
"PUT -d RANDOM``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/developers/remote-users.rst:17
msgid ""
"For a list of possible values, please find enum ``DevShibAccountType`` in"
" the source code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/developers/remote-users.rst:19
msgid ""
"Now when you go to http://localhost:8080/shib.xhtml you should be "
"prompted to create a Shibboleth account."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/developers/remote-users.rst:21
msgid ""
"OAuth is much more straightforward to get working on your laptop than "
"Shibboleth. GitHub is a good identity provider to test with because you "
"can easily request a Client ID and Client Secret that works against "
"localhost. Follow the instructions in the :doc:`/installation/oauth2` "
"section of the installation Guide and use "
"\"http://localhost:8080/oauth2/callback.xhtml\" as the callback URL."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/developers/remote-users.rst:23
msgid ""
"In addition to setting up OAuth on your laptop for real (as in "
":doc:`/installation/oauth2`), you can also use a dev/debug mode:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/developers/remote-users.rst:25
msgid ""
"``curl http://localhost:8080/api/admin/settings/:DebugOAuthAccountType -X"
" PUT -d RANDOM_EMAIL2``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/developers/remote-users.rst:27
msgid ""
"For a list of possible values, please find enum ``DevOAuthAccountType`` "
"in the source code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/developers/remote-users.rst:29
msgid ""
"Now when you go to http://localhost:8080/firstLogin.xhtml you should be "
"prompted to create a Shibboleth account."
msgstr ""

